Calculus does not come easily to me, but Javid makes coming to lecture enjoyable! The material is difficult and goes fast if you don't have much experience, but that means you need to work harder. He's extremely helpful if you go talk to him after class, and a really nice and funny guy.
He is fantastic. No other teacher here engages his students and keeps them focused like he does. Humorous. Intelligent. Energetic. Cannot ask for more from a professor.
One of the best calculus teachers at U of I. You definitely should take his class! Easy to understand and really funny.

Great teacher that keeps the class entertaining with his jokes. Javid does a really good job explaining the concepts gone over in class by providing many examples. He makes a seemingly difficult topic easy to understand and enjoyable.
perfect.

As someone from the "YOLO" generation, I've often struggled to find reasons to persevere through the eternal struggle of a middle-upper class suburban life. Then, I met the talented and handsome professor,Javid Validashti. Now I know that my life's purpose is to retake this class for all of eternity, regardless of my grade. I know it's worth it.
